President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, said on Wednesday that  the National Assembly had started consultations with the executive arm of government on a new version of the Petroleum Industry Bill to be introduced in the 9th National Assembly. Lawan, according to a statement by his media aide,  Ezrel Tabiowo,  stated this  during a meeting with  the representatives of the International Monetary Fund who paid a visit to his office at the National Assembly, Abuja. The statement listed the representatives of  the IMF delegation to include  the Senior Resident Representative Mission Chief for Nigeria, Amine Mati; Jesmine Raman; Zainab Mangga; Nanrup Ibrahim; Osana Odonye; and Harrison Okafor. Copyright PUNCH.
